        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Browser QA should become a preset workflow once constrained jobs exist, not a separate bespoke testing framework.",
        "Useful checks include route load, expected text/control visibility, no console errors, no failed network requests, and screenshot on failure."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define a QA job preset that expands to constrained job steps and assertions rather than adding new browser semantics.",
        "Include standard checks for page load, expected content/control visibility, console errors, failed network requests, and failure screenshots/artifacts.",
        "Return compact pass/fail evidence with categories and nextActions suitable for agents writing reproducible issue reports.",
        "Add docs and tests showing when to use QA mode versus raw browser commands or custom jobs."
      ],
